            <title>[MATH-1167] OLSMultipleLinearRegression STILL needs a way to specify non-zero singularity threshold when instantiating QRDecomposition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1167</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A fix was made for this issue in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1110&quot; title=&quot;OLSMultipleLinearRegression needs a way to specify non-zero singularity threshold when instantiating QRDecomposition&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MATH-1110&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MATH-1110&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the newSampleData method but not for the newXSampleData method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a simple change to propagate the threshold to QRDecomposition:&lt;br/&gt;
237c237&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;         qr = new QRDecomposition(getX());&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8212;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;         qr = new QRDecomposition(getX(), threshold);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;jdk1.7_71, OSX 10.10&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
